http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Man-drowns-while-cleaning-well/article14021638.ece

A 23-year-old youth drowned when he, along with his friend, went down to clean a well filled with filth in Siddapura on Tuesday.The deceased has been identified as Iyaz, a resident of Krishnamurthy Colony here and a carpenter by profession.According to the police, the owner of a service centre in Wilson Garden asked the two men to clean the well.Iyaz and Salehuddin went down the well at around 5 p.m. Iyaz suddenly fell into the well, while Salehuddin managed to climb out.He was rushed to the hospital by passersby, who alerted the police.The Fire and Emergency Services personnel recovered the body, which was shifted to the Kempegowda Institute of Medical Science (KIMS) Hospital for post-mortem.“The well was situated close to a fuel station and the air smelled of petrol. Inhaling the air for a considerable amount of time could have caused Iyaz to fall unconscious,” a Fire Department official said.”Siddapura police have registered a case of negligence against the owner of Veena Service Centre.